Phase 1 complete. Here's what was built and the status:

---

**Behavioral Compliance Gate** (`~/.claude/hooks/behavioral-compliance-gate.sh` — Stop hook)

Three violation types, all escalating through NOTICE → WARNING → CRITICAL:
- **Hesitation** (`should I`, `want me to`, `let me know if`, etc.) — exempt when destructive ops context detected
- **Half-measure** (single-GPU language on multi-GPU hosts)
- **Repeat instruction** — new VIOLATION 3: extracts last user message from transcript, keyword fingerprint (4+ char words, 40% overlap threshold, 3 keyword minimum), matches against `instruction-log.jsonl`, injects the matched prior instruction text

**Resource Utilization Directive** (`~/.claude/hooks/preflight-check.sh` — SessionStart hook)

The remote already had a more comprehensive version: parallel SSH to gpu-server-1/gpu-server-2/gpu-server-3, K3s cluster check, Ollama loaded models, service health. The GPU multi-idle directive fires when a host has 2+ GPUs with any GPU <500 MiB used. Current fleet: gpu-server-3 has 2× RTX 5080 at 60% each — no false positive.

**Anti-Repeat State Tracker** (`~/.claude/hooks/state/instruction-log.jsonl`)

Populated on every Stop hook invocation. Capped at 500 entries with automatic trim.

**settings.json** — both hooks already registered by prior session; no settings change needed.

**Pushed:** `5863138` to `your-github-user/claude-config`
